OL,3,CWoman diagnosed with rare condition
OL,4,Cafter doctors said she was just drunk
OL,6,FA dietitian suggested a low-
OL,7,Fcarbohydrate diet, and after
OL,8,Fcompleting a one-month course of an
OL,9,Fantifungal medication and the diet,
OL,10,Fthe woman's symptoms went away and
OL,11,Fremained absent for four months.
OL,13,FThe woman slowly started to eat
OL,14,Fcarbohydrates again, but one month
OL,15,Fafter doing so she had a recurrence of
OL,16,Fslurred speech and drowsiness, which
OL,17,Fled to a fall.
OL,19,FShe was advised to restart the low-
OL,20,Fcarbohydrate diet again, and her
OL,21,Fsymptoms resolved.
